---
/**
 * rest-api/0001 · Figure 2 — "what statelessness buys you".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/rest-api/lessons/0001-what-makes-an-api-restful.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). Lives as an .astro component for the same reason
 * as Fig1: raw inline SVG with kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside MDX,
 * but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 *
 * Uses the arw + arwG arrowhead markers (the source defines them once in a shared
 * body-level <svg><defs>); they're embedded here in a local <defs> so the figure
 * renders self-contained (ids + fills unchanged).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Two self-contained requests carrying their own tokens are routed by a load balancer to different stateless server nodes; no session is stored"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwG"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#2f5d3a"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text
                x="320"
                y="18"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#111110">EACH REQUEST IS SELF-CONTAINED · NO SERVER SESSION</text
            >
            <!-- client -->
            <rect
                x="10"
                y="60"
                width="120"
                height="80"
                rx="9"
                fill="#f1eee2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"></rect>
            <text x="70" y="86" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Client</text
            >
            <text x="70" y="106" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >attaches token</text
            >
            <text x="70" y="120" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >+ context to</text
            >
            <text x="70" y="134" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >every request</text
            >
            <!-- request 1 -->
            <line x1="130" y1="84" x2="232" y2="84" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="181" y="77" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >GET /me · Bearer …</text
            >
            <!-- request 2 -->
            <line x1="130" y1="120" x2="232" y2="120" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"
            ></line>
            <text x="181" y="135" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >GET /me · Bearer …</text
            >
            <!-- load balancer -->
            <rect x="234" y="68" width="100" height="64" rx="9" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"></rect>
            <text
                x="284"
                y="96"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">Load</text
            >
            <text
                x="284"
                y="110"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10.5"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#1f3a5a">balancer</text
            >
            <!-- to node A -->
            <line x1="334" y1="86" x2="470" y2="64" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"></line>
            <!-- to node B -->
            <line x1="334" y1="114" x2="470" y2="146" stroke="#2f5d3a" marker-end="url(#arwG)"
            ></line>
            <!-- node A -->
            <rect x="472" y="40" width="158" height="48" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="551"
                y="60"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Server node A</text
            >
            <text x="551" y="76" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >holds no session ✓</text
            >
            <!-- node B -->
            <rect x="472" y="122" width="158" height="48" rx="9" fill="#eef5ee" stroke="#2f5d3a"
            ></rect>
            <text
                x="551"
                y="142"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="11"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">Server node B</text
            >
            <text x="551" y="158" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#244a2e"
                >holds no session ✓</text
            >
            <text x="320" y="192" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#7a1f12"
                >Because no node "remembers" you, both requests are interchangeable — that is
                horizontal scale.</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Statelessness is what lets the layered system work: any node, any time, any request.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
